Key Match Events: Azeddine Ounahi opened the scoring in the 8th minute
Chadi Riad doubled the lead by the 16th minute
Ayoub El Kaabi scored a hat-trick against Congo Brazzaville, scoring at the 20th, 39th, and 53rd minutes
Forward Soufiane Rahimi closed the scoring with a sixth goal in the 62nd minute
Pre-Game Insights: The Moroccan coach Walid Regragui instructed the players to step up the game, and they responded brilliantly
The team was showing signs of fatigue, so they used this opportunity to give some playing time to others
Post-Match Reflections: The Moroccan coach Walid Regragui is very happy with the group's overall performance, but they understand there's still work to be done
The coach also singled out Brahim Diaz and Soufiane Rahimi for praise, highlighting Rahimi's goal shortly after coming on as a substitute
Miscellaneous Highlights: This dominant performance puts Morocco at the top of Group E with 9 points
Tanzania sits in second with 6 points, followed by Niger and Zambia with 3 points each
Congo Brazzaville and Eritrea remain scoreless
Others: The Moroccan national football team dominated their match against Congo Brazzaville, securing a resounding 6-0 victory on Tuesday at Adrar Stadium in Agadir
